          <h2>
           <a href="http://one.arch.tamu.edu/news/2018/6/29/laup-prof-leads-tedx-talk-why-sustainability-efforts-fail/">
            LAUP prof delivers TEDx Talk defining 'uncanny wisdom'
           </a>
          </h2>
          <div class="publication-date">
           <span>
            posted
           </span>
           Fri, 29 Jun 2018
          </div>
          <div class="description">
           Seemingly rational choices, made in the wake of natural disasters, can produce unsound results due to “uncanny wisdom,” a term, coined by a Texas A&amp;M urban planning professor, describing actions that eventually exacerbate problems they were meant to solve.
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
